# Switch/Case with Objects

When you have many possible values, an object lookup can be cleaner than a long if/else chain.

```jsx
const messageMap = {
  success: <SuccessIcon />,
  error: <ErrorIcon />,
  warning: <WarningIcon />,
  info: <InfoIcon />
};

return <div>{messageMap[status] || <DefaultIcon />}</div>;
```

This is efficient and easy to extend.

